 - 2026-07-16: Wrangler `whoami` may exit successfully while printing that the user is unauthenticated. Authentication detection therefore parses the command output, Auto mode uses `--temporary` when unauthenticated, and retries with `--temporary` if non-interactive authentication disappears during deployment.
 - 2026-07-16: User-facing sidebar, notifications, commands and settings support English and Simplified Chinese. `solodrop.language` defaults to following the VS Code display language and rerenders the sidebar immediately when changed.
 - 2026-07-16: The sidebar header exposes a direct `中` / `EN` language toggle. It writes the selected language to the global VS Code `solodrop.language` setting, so the choice persists across reloads, restarts and workspaces.
+- 2026-07-16: Recent-share metadata uses VS Code Settings Sync so the same signed-in user can see one list across devices. Local source paths are kept in a separate unsynced mapping; expired temporary shares reuse that local source when available and otherwise ask the user to choose the file before running the existing share flow.
 
 ## Decisions
 
 - 2026-07-16: The product is an agent-artifact delivery layer, not a thin Cloudflare Drop wrapper. Format conversion, recipient readability, leak prevention and verified delivery are the product value.
 - 2026-07-16: Auto deployment uses an authenticated Wrangler account when available and otherwise uses Cloudflare temporary deployment. Temporary links must be claimed within 60 minutes; custom expiry and private access are not presented as current features.
+- 2026-07-16: Temporary entries derive an explicit 60-minute claim-window expiry, display active/expired status in Recent, and expose Share again only after expiry.
 - 2026-07-16: The Logo source of truth is `resources/logo.svg`; `resources/logo.png` is the Marketplace raster derivative. The sidebar follows VS Code semantic theme tokens and maintains one primary action.
 
 ## Current Handoff
